{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Increase the Lifetime ISA house price limit in line with inflation ",
        "additional_details": "We think the \u00a3450,000 limit, set in 2017, no longer reflects housing affordability. UK house prices have risen by around 25%, with London\u2019s average now around \u00a3525,000. We believe many first-time buyers are unable to use the Lifetime ISA to purchase in high-cost areas, limiting access to government assistance for young buyers. We think an updated limit would help bridge the gap in today\u2019s housing market.",
        "background": "Adjust the Lifetime ISA house price limit to reflect current market values, allowing first-time buyers in high-cost areas access to homes under this program.",
